---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
// cspell:ignore tlsv
const brewInstall = 'brew install santi020k/tap/santi020k-terminal && santi020k-terminal configure'
const scriptInstall = 'curl --proto \'=https\' --tlsv1.2 -fsSL https://terminal.santi020k.com/zsh/install.zsh | zsh'
const restart = 'exec zsh'
const headings = [{ id: 'requirements', label: 'Requirements' }, { id: 'install', label: 'Install with Homebrew' }, { id: 'script', label: 'Install script' }, { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next steps' }]
---
<DocsLayout title="Getting started" description="Install the complete Santi020k terminal setup on macOS, then choose the prompt and terminal colors that fit your workflow." path="/docs/" {headings}>
  <aside class="docs-callout"><b>Homebrew is recommended</b><p>It owns the CLI, theme assets, shell completions, and dependencies, making updates and removal predictable.</p></aside>
  <section id="requirements"><h2>Before you install</h2><ul><li>Use macOS with Zsh as your interactive shell.</li><li>Install Homebrew and make sure <code>brew</code> is available in your shell.</li><li>Use a Nerd Font if you want the Powerline prompt symbols.</li></ul></section>
  <section id="install"><h2>Install the complete setup</h2><p>Install the formula, then explicitly apply the managed configuration:</p><div class="command"><code>{brewInstall}</code><button data-copy={brewInstall} aria-label="Copy Homebrew installation command">Copy</button></div><p>The installer backs up files it manages, writes configuration to <code>~/.config/santi020k-terminal</code>, and adds one source line to your existing <code>~/.zshrc</code>. Start a fresh session when it finishes:</p><div class="command"><code>{restart}</code><button data-copy={restart} aria-label="Copy Zsh restart command">Copy</button></div></section>
  <section id="script"><h2>Use the hosted installer</h2><p>If you prefer the direct setup path, this installs the same Homebrew dependencies and downloads the current configuration:</p><div class="command"><code>{scriptInstall}</code><button data-copy={scriptInstall} aria-label="Copy hosted installation command">Copy</button></div><p><a href="/zsh/install.zsh" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the installer source <span class="external-mark" aria-hidden="true">↗</span><span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a> before running it if you want to inspect every operation.</p></section>
  <section id="next-steps"><h2>Make it yours</h2><div class="docs-link-list"><a href="/docs/zsh/"><b>Understand the Zsh setup</b><span>Plugins, tools, history, and managed configuration.</span></a><a href="/docs/starship/"><b>Choose a prompt preset</b><span>Compare rich, portable, and minimal Starship configurations.</span></a><a href="/docs/terminal-colors/"><b>Install terminal colors</b><span>Apply the dark or light palette to your terminal application.</span></a><a href="/docs/cli/"><b>Learn the CLI</b><span>Switch presets, check status, update, repair, or uninstall.</span></a></div></section>
</DocsLayout>
